===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|目|木|糸|ls=ic}} - to hang with the string 糸 by the head 目 (using an eye to represent a head) on a tree 木. Originally referred to {{och-l|懸|to hang}}; later {{liushu|j|nocap=y}} for {{och-l|縣|administrative division}}.

In Qin bamboo slip scripts, some of {{Han compound|目|木}} were corrupted to {{zh-l|*県}} (with one straight horizontal line rather than {{zh-l|*𠃊}}) which interpreted to a reversed head {{zh-l|*𥄉}} by ''{{w|Shuowen}}'', and 糸 was corrupted to {{zh-l|*系}}.

